on, Jessica, and Alicia?seven girls coming of age in poverty.This is a moving story about girls who have lost their childhoods, but who face the street's torments with courage and resiliency. "I want out," says 10-year-old Blair, a tiny but tough girl who is extremely poor and yet deeply imaginative and precocious. Hicks tries to convey to her students a sense of the power of fiction and of sisterhood to get them through the toughest years of adolescence. But by the time they're sixteen, eight years after the start of the class, the girls are experiencing the collision of their youthful dreams with the pitfalls of growing up in chaotic single-parent families amid the deteriorating cityscape. Yet even as they face disappointments and sometimes despair, these girls cling to their desire for a better future. The author's own life story-from a poorly educated girl in a small mountain town to a Harvard-educated writer, teacher, and social advocate-infuses this chronicle with a message of hope.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aPoor girlsxAnecdotesxOhioxCincinnati. 0aPoor girlsxBooks and readingxOhioxCincinnati. 0aPoor girlsxBooks and readingzOhiozCincinnati. 0aPoor girlsxEducationxOhioxCincinnati. 0aPoor girlsxEducationzOhiozCincinnati. 0aPoor girlszOhiozCincinnativAnecdotes. 0aPoor whitesxEducationxOhioxCincinnati. 0aPoor whitesxEducationzOhiozCincinnati. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953710423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520953710.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978